§ Main result ⦉
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ $M ⊂ 𝗥^{n}$ is affine if and only if there exists $b ∈
    𝗥^m$ and $B ∈ 𝗥^{m × n}$ such that
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ M = \Set*{x ∈ 𝗥^{n}}{Bx = b}. ⦉
    ⦉⦉
</statement>
